{"sectionId":757,"sectionIdLiteral":"757","humanId":"lesson-334","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"Today I claim the gifts forgiveness gives.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 334"},"annotation":"W-334","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-334\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"757#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"757#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>I will not wait another day to find the treasures that my Father offers me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"757#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Illusions are all vain, and dreams are gone even while they are woven out of thoughts that rest on false perceptions.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"757#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Let me not accept such meager gifts again today.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"757#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>God‚Äôs Voice is offering the peace of God to all who hear and choose to follow Him.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"757#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>This is my choice today.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"757#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>And so I go to find the treasures God has given me.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"757#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"757#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>I seek but the eternal.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"757#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>For Your Son can be content with nothing less than this.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"757#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>What, then, can be his solace but what You are offering to his bewildered mind and frightened heart, to give him certainty and bring him peace?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"757#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Today I would behold my brother sinless.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"757#2:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>This Your Will for me, for so will I behold my sinlessness.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"I wi